Perfect. So the chat is a full Gemini conversation where the logs are a tool Gemini can call — it decides when to search your logs, retrieves relevant chunks from pgvector, and weaves it into the response naturally. That's a cleaner UX than forced RAG anyway.

Now I have everything. Writing the full implementation doc now 👇

---

```markdown
# Remmy — Implementation Plan

> Personal multimodal daily logger with audio and image capture,
> AI-powered understanding, pgvector semantic storage, and Gemini-powered
> chat with access to your logs as a tool.

---

## Tech Stack

### Frontend
- React (PWA, mobile-first from day 1)
- shadcn/ui — component library
- lucide-animated — icons
- Light theme throughout
- Service worker + web manifest for PWA install

### Backend
- Go — already structured
- Gin/Echo (existing setup)
- PostgreSQL with pgvector extension
- Cloudflare R2 — audio and image file storage
- Gemini API — understanding layer + chat

### Infrastructure
- Docker — switch base postgres image to pgvector
- R2 already configured
- All AI models are empty interfaces / whitebox stubs unless specified

---

## Phase 0 — Infrastructure Setup

### 0.1 Switch Postgres to pgvector

Update docker-compose.yml to use pgvector image:

```yaml
services:
  db:
    image: pgvector/pgvector:pg16
    environment:
      POSTGRES_USER: remmy
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: remmy
      POSTGRES_DB: remmy
    ports:
      - "5432:5432"
    volumes:
      - pgdata:/var/lib/postgresql/data
```

Enable extension in migration:

```sql
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS vector;
```

### 0.2 Database Schema

```sql
-- logs table
CREATE TABLE logs (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  user_id UUID NOT NULL,
  type VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL CHECK (type IN ('audio', 'image')),
  raw_file_url TEXT NOT NULL,
  raw_transcript TEXT,
  raw_description TEXT,
  rewritten_content TEXT,
  embedding vector(1536),
  habit_matches TEXT[],
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  logged_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- habits table (schema only, UI skipped for now)
CREATE TABLE habits (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  user_id UUID NOT NULL,
  name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- index for vector similarity search
CREATE INDEX ON logs USING ivfflat (embedding vector_cosine_ops)
  WITH (lists = 100);

-- index for date-based feed queries
CREATE INDEX ON logs (user_id, logged_at DESC);
```

### 0.3 R2 Bucket Structure

```
remmy/
  audio/
    {user_id}/
      {log_id}.webm
  images/
    {user_id}/
      {log_id}.jpg
```

### 0.4 Environment Variables

```env
DATABASE_URL=postgres://remmy:remmy@localhost:5432/remmy
R2_ACCOUNT_ID=
R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
R2_BUCKET_NAME=remmy
R2_PUBLIC_URL=
GEMINI_API_KEY=
```

