## Phase 1 — File Ingestion API

### 1.1 Upload Endpoint

```
POST /api/v1/logs/audio
Content-Type: multipart/form-data
Body: file (audio/webm or audio/mp4)

POST /api/v1/logs/image
Content-Type: multipart/form-data
Body: file (image/jpeg or image/png or image/webp)
```

**Flow:**
1. Receive file
2. Validate type and size (audio max 50mb, image max 20mb)
3. Generate log UUID
4. Upload raw file to R2 at correct path
5. Create log record in postgres with status pending
6. Enqueue processing job
7. Return log ID and status immediately (async processing)

**Response:**
```json
{
  "id": "uuid",
  "type": "audio",
  "status": "processing",
  "created_at": "2025-01-01T00:00:00Z"
}
```

### 1.2 Job Queue

Use a simple Go channel-based worker pool for now — no external queue needed at this scale.

```go
type ProcessingJob struct {
    LogID   string
    LogType string
    FileURL string
}
```

Worker picks up job → runs pipeline → updates log record

### 1.3 Feed Endpoint

```
GET /api/v1/logs?date=2025-01-01
```

Returns all logs for a given day ordered chronologically.

```json
{
  "logs": [
    {
      "id": "uuid",
      "type": "audio",
      "raw_file_url": "https://...",
      "rewritten_content": "...",
      "habit_matches": ["gym", "reading"],
      "logged_at": "2025-01-01T09:14:00Z",
      "status": "ready"
    }
  ]
}
```

