## Implementation Order for Claude Code

Build in this exact order — each phase is testable before moving to next:

1. Phase 0 — docker pgvector, schema migrations, env setup
2. Phase 1 — upload endpoints, R2 storage, job queue, feed endpoint
3. Phase 2 — stub ASR interface and pipeline
4. Phase 3 — stub vision interface and pipeline
5. Phase 4 — Gemini understanding layer, chunking, pgvector storage
6. Phase 5 — feed UI, PWA setup, audio/image capture, log detail page
7. Phase 6 — Gemini chat with log search tool, chat UI
8. Phase 7 — digest generation, email send, digest UI

---

## Notes for Claude Code

- All AI model interfaces must be defined as Go interfaces — never call
  models directly from handlers, always go through the interface
- The stub implementations must be the default until real models are
  wired in — never block on model availability
- Mobile first means every component is designed at 375px width first,
  then scaled up — not the other way around
- All API responses must include proper error shapes:
  ```json
  { "error": "message", "code": "error_code" }
  ```
- Use pgvector cosine distance operator (<=>), not L2
- R2 uploads should be server-side only — never expose R2 credentials
  to the frontend
- All file uploads go through the Go backend, not directly to R2
- PWA must work offline for the feed (cache last 7 days of logs)
  using service worker cache strategy
```

